<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Tribute Page</title>
<style>
body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #42275a, #734b6d);
    color: #222;
}
nav {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
    padding: 14px;
    text-align: center;
}
nav a {
    color: #fff;
    margin: 0 18px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: 0.3s;
}
nav a:hover { 
    color: #ffcc70; 
}

.container {
    width: 75%;
    margin: 50px auto;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.95);
    padding: 25px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
}
h1, h2 {
    text-align: center;
    color: #42275a;
}
img {
    display: block;
    margin: 20px auto;
    width: 220px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 4px solid #734b6d;
    transition: transform 0.3s;
}
img:hover {
    transform: scale(1.05);
}
p {
    text-align: justify;
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding: 0 10px;
}
footer {
    text-align: center;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.8);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 10px;
    margin-top: 20px;
    font-size: 14px;
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<nav>
    <a href="#">Home</a>
    <a href="#">Biography</a>
    <a href="#">Teachings</a>
</nav>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Swami Vivekananda</h1>

    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6f/Swami_Vivekananda.jpg" alt="Swami Vivekananda">

    <h2>About</h2>
    <p>
        Swami Vivekananda was a great Indian monk and philosopher who introduced Indian
        spirituality to the Western world. He was a key figure in the revival of Hinduism
        in India and inspired millions through his teachings on strength, confidence, and service.
    </p>

    <h2>Contributions</h2>
    <p>
        He represented India at the Chicago Parliament of Religions in 1893, where his speech
        gained worldwide recognition. He founded the Ramakrishna Mission and emphasized the
        importance of education, self-belief, and helping others.
    </p>
</div>

<footer>
    Tribute Page | Created for Academic Project
</footer>

</body>
</html>
